%N A395778 Squarefree numbers k with least prime factor p and m distinct prime factors, such that not all larger prime factors q > p are less than p^m.
%C A395778 Local complement of A393644 in A120944.
%C A395778 Let lpf = A020639, omega = A001221, and pi = A000720.
%C A395778 Smallest a(n) with omega(a(n)) = m is A002110(m-1)*prime(1+pi(2^m)) = A002110(m-1)*A014210(m).
%H A395778 Michael De Vlieger, <a href="/A395778/b395778.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%e A395778 Table of n, a(n) for select n:
%e A395778       n      a(n)
%e A395778   ----------------------------------------
